                         ** Release Information **

    Game Notes:
    ~~~~~~~~~~~
    F1 2001 shook the house with precision, speed, and insanely tight racing.
    Not ones to pass up a good thing, EA does its capitalizing thing and
    extends the franchise into 2002.

    Muscle your way to the front and enjoy every heart-stopping moment as you
    battle for every inch of track against the superstars of the sport. With
    authentic driver controls, you experience life in the cockpit with the same
    technological wizardry available to this season?s Formula One racers, or
    switch off the controls and rely on your raw driving skills. Take the
    wheel in F1 2002 and take aim at the 2002 Formula One World Championship.

    Real drivers, teams, cars, and tracks all taken straight from the actual
    2002 racing season, will once again make appearances. Aside from this,
    and all of the other options and nuances to make return appearances,
    F1 2002 will also include:

    Game Features:
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    * 2002 Season complete with new Toyota and Renault racing teams.

    * Telemetry based optimization of vehicle setup, driving style,
      and performance.

    * New graphics technology that incorporates multi-texturing, dynamic
      weather, real-world lighting, character and pit crew animations,
      and "6D physics" (now including engine and brake temperature modeling).

    * Greater accessibility, automation, and controller compatibility.

    * As with practically all of EA's marquee sports franchises, yearly
      iterations are but improvements upon the last efforts, and not
      necessarily radical alterations to or departures from proven formulas.
      And, as with practically all of EA's other marquee sports franchises,
      this is usually a damn good thing. F1 2001 was an exercise in immense
      satisfaction; I can only imagine 2002 will be the same, but better.

Later edit: THE "CATASTROPHIC FAILURE" FIX
------------------------------------------
(Thanks to big-oinker for finding the solution)

"Copy all files and folders to your harddrive (I put it all in a few folder i called f1 2002), then select all files and folders and change the properties on them (write protected on, then apply then write protected off, then apply) so they ain't write protected.

Then just start the game (not the installer) and it should launch the 3D Setup program, select video mode and let the 3D Setup test the mode and select finished, then the game should start.

The reason for the change of the write protection is to make sure the 3D Setup saves the config file."
